# Project Rules ‚Äî Group Travel Aggregator

## 1. TypeScript Strictness

- Never use `any` in production code ‚Äî use `unknown` + type guards
- Never use `as unknown as X` double-casts:
  - ‚ùå `req.query as unknown as MyType`
  - ‚úÖ `req.query as MyType` (validate middleware already parses it)
  - ‚úÖ `as any` in tests for mock constructor injection
  - If you need `as unknown as`, the types are wrong ‚Äî fix them
- No `@ts-ignore` or `@ts-expect-error` without a comment explaining why
- Strict mode enabled (`strict: true` in tsconfig)
- Named exports only ‚Äî no default exports (easier refactoring, better IDE support)

## 2. Architecture ‚Äî Layered Pattern

- **Never skip the Service layer:** Controller ‚Üí Service ‚Üí Repository (never Controller ‚Üí Repository)
- **Controllers are thin:** parse request + call service + send response (max ~15 lines per method)
- **All business logic lives in services** (max ~30 lines per method, split if longer)
- **DB queries ONLY in repositories** ‚Äî services never write raw Prisma queries
- **Use Dependency Injection** ‚Äî services receive repos via constructor
- **Use asyncHandler wrapper** ‚Äî no try-catch in controllers
- **Throw typed errors** (NotFoundError, ForbiddenError, ValidationError) ‚Äî never silently swallow
- **Use Pino logger** ‚Äî no `console.log` in production code
- **Constants in constants.ts** ‚Äî no magic numbers/strings in code

## 3. API Response Format

- Success: `{ success: true, data: {...}, pagination?: {...} }`
- Error: `{ success: false, error: { code: "MACHINE_READABLE", message: "Human readable" } }`
- Validate all inputs at the edge with Zod schemas on every endpoint
- Webhook routes use separate pipeline: no CORS, no auth middleware, raw body for HMAC verification

## 4. Frontend ‚Äî Component Rules

- Props interface above component ‚Äî new dev sees the contract first
- Hook order inside components: hooks ‚Üí derived state ‚Üí handlers ‚Üí return
- Import order: external ‚Üí internal ‚Üí types ‚Üí styles
- Use `cn()` from shadcn/ui utils for conditional Tailwind classes
- No inline styles ‚Äî Tailwind only (exception: truly dynamic values like `style={{ width: `${percent}%` }}`)
- Co-locate unit tests next to source: `trip-card.test.tsx` next to `trip-card.tsx`

## 5. Frontend ‚Äî 4-State Rendering (Mandatory)

Every data-fetching component MUST handle all 4 states:
```
if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />       // Skeleton matching component shape
if (error)     return <ErrorState />     // With retry button
if (!data)     return <EmptyState />     // With relevant action
return         <ActualComponent />       // Happy path
```

Three layers of error handling:
1. Route-level error boundaries (Next.js `error.tsx`)
2. Component-level error boundaries (isolate failures)
3. Data-fetching error states (TanStack Query inline)

## 6. Frontend ‚Äî Query Keys & Data Fetching

- Use query key factory pattern: `tripKeys.list(filters)`, never inline strings
- Query key factories live in `lib/query-keys.ts` ‚Äî single source of truth
- Mutations must invalidate related queries in `onSuccess`
- Custom hooks encapsulate all data fetching ‚Äî never call `apiClient` directly in components

## 7. Design System ‚Äî Colors (WCAG AA Compliance)

- **NEVER use `primary-500` for body text on white** ‚Äî fails WCAG AA (3.1:1 < 4.5:1)
- Use `primary-600` or `primary-700` for links and text on white backgrounds
- `primary-500` ONLY for: button backgrounds, large headlines (‚â•18px bold), icons, badges
- Same rule for `accent` and `highlight` ‚Äî use `700` shade for text on white
- Semantic colors: `500` for text, `50` for background (e.g., `text-success-500 bg-success-50`)
- Never hardcode hex values ‚Äî always use design tokens from `tokens.json`
- New colors/spacing ‚Üí add to `tokens.json` first, never directly in a component

## 8. Design System ‚Äî Skeletons & Loading

- Use `.skeleton` CSS class for shimmer loading ‚Äî never `animate-pulse`
- Skeletons must match the shape of the component they replace
- Button loading: disable button + show spinner left of text
- Full page loading: centered spinner with `min-h-[50vh]`

## 9. Design System ‚Äî Animation Rules

- No arbitrary animation values ‚Äî register in `tailwind.config.ts`, fallback in `globals.css`
- Keep animations ‚â§ 0.6s ‚Äî longer feels sluggish on mobile
- Infinite animations ONLY for loading indicators ‚Äî never for UI chrome
- GPU-promote animated elements with `will-change-transform`
- Never bypass `prefers-reduced-motion` with inline styles ‚Äî all animations via CSS classes

## 10. Design System ‚Äî Typography

- Font pairing: Plus Jakarta Sans (display headings), Inter (body), JetBrains Mono (codes/prices)
- `h1`, `h2`, `h3` use `font-display` ‚Äî everything else uses `font-sans` (Inter)

## 11. Design System ‚Äî Spacing & Layout

- All spacing is multiples of 4px ‚Äî never arbitrary values
- Max content width: 1280px (`max-w-7xl`)
- Card grid: 3 columns desktop, 2 tablet, 1 mobile

## 12. Mobile-First (Mandatory)

- Write mobile styles as the **default** (no breakpoint prefix)
- Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` prefixes to enhance for larger screens
- Never build desktop-first then "fix" mobile
- Tables on mobile ‚Üí stacked cards
- Side-by-side on mobile ‚Üí stack vertically (`flex-col` ‚Üí `md:flex-row`)
- Test every page at 375px width before done

## 13. Dark Mode

- Do NOT add `dark:` variants until the dark token set is finalized (Phase 2)

## 14. Security

- No hardcoded secrets, API keys, or tokens ‚Äî `.env` only, validated with Zod at startup
- Never log PII (passwords, tokens, Aadhaar, credit card numbers)
- User input sanitized: Zod `.trim()`, `.toLowerCase()` for emails
- No raw string concatenation in queries ‚Äî Prisma parameterized or `$executeRaw` with template literals
- bcrypt with salt rounds ‚â• 12
- Refresh tokens stored as SHA-256 hashes ‚Äî never store raw
- Images NEVER route through Express ‚Äî Cloudinary direct upload with signed URLs

## 15. Naming Conventions

| Item | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Files | kebab-case | `trip-card.tsx`, `booking.service.ts` |
| Components | PascalCase | `TripCard`, `BookingForm` |
| Functions | camelCase | `createBooking`, `handlePayment` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `MAX_GROUP_SIZE`, `ESCROW_HOLD_DAYS` |
| Types/Interfaces | PascalCase | `TripSummary`, `CreateBookingDto` |
| API routes | kebab-case | `/api/v1/my-trips` |
| Env vars | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET` |

## 16. Git Conventions

- Branch: `feat/trip-search`, `fix/booking-escrow`, `chore/update-deps`
- Commits: conventional format ‚Äî `feat: add trip comparison page`, `fix: handle duplicate webhook`
- PR size: max ~300 lines changed

## 17. Database

- Soft-delete on all tables (except audit: PaymentTransaction, WebhookEvent, RefreshToken, VerificationCode)
- All prices in whole rupees (`Int`, not `Float`)
- Never edit a committed migration ‚Äî create a new one
- Add new columns as nullable first
- One migration per feature, named descriptively (`add-payment-transaction-table`)
- Prisma commands (generate, migrate, seed) run inside Docker: `docker compose exec api npx prisma <command>`

## 18. Testing

- Every public method MUST have tests ‚Äî tests are first-class deliverables
- One `describe` block per public service method, happy path always first
- Naming: `"should <expected outcome> when <condition>"`
- Arrange ‚Üí Act ‚Üí Assert pattern, `vi.clearAllMocks()` in `beforeEach`
- BE minimum per method: happy path, not-found, authorization, validation, edge cases
- FE minimum per component: loading, error, empty, data states
- Test data via factory functions ‚Äî override only relevant fields, deterministic dates

## 19. Workflow Discipline

- **Always create a todo list before implementing** ‚Äî break the task into small, trackable steps using the todo_list tool
- **After implementation is complete**, go through every rule in this file and confirm all are satisfied before marking the task as done
